1
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:45,520
{\an8}I want you to be my model.

2
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:49,000
{\an8}The tears today, they'll turn into a fire

3
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:52,560
{\an8}that will burn the enemy
until not even a soul remains.

4
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:53,920
{\an8}<i>Buy his trust first, Rin.</i>

5
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,800
{\an8}<i>Act like bait,</i>

6
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:59,520
{\an8}<i>draw everything out of him,</i>

7
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:00,800
{\an8}<i>then deal with him.</i>

8
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:07,120
You love each other, right? You're dead!

9
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:13,280
- Oh!
- Whoa!

10
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:15,480
Hey!

11
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,440
Pat!

12
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:21,680
Sun.

13
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:39,040
Pat, are you okay?

14
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:41,320
It hurts.

15
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:56,240
Stop! One more move and you're dead!

16
00:03:56,320 --> 00:04:00,400
Didn't I teach you, Khanin?
Shoot first, talk later.

17
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:03,200
Why are you trying to kill Taiga again?

18
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:06,360
Fire Phoenix already ruined his life,
destroyed his family once.

19
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:09,640
I know you're a good subordinate.

20
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:13,680
But I didn't expect
you'd be loyal to every boss.

21
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,720
Even a dog's ashamed.

22
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:20,240
And you? Why do you help Taiga?

23
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:22,200
Have you ever asked yourself?

24
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:25,080
Are you helping because you really care

25
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:30,040
or just taking one man's revenge
and twisting it

26
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,560
for your own gain?

27
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,560
You want revenge for your family, right?

28
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:38,600
If you fail, you'll never face
your parents in the grave.

29
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:43,400
Stop talking about my family like that!

30
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,240
Your stupid grief

31
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:49,680
is dragging Taiga straight to hell,

32
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:53,960
with your dad, mom, and sister!

33
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:03,920
Punlop!

34
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:10,120
Ugh!

35
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:20,680
Geez!

36
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,040
Damn it!

37
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,320
The media won't cover us.

38
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,760
They'll focus on jealousy instead.

39
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:41,640
And the others?

40
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:44,200
Police are clearing the area.

41
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:47,280
But I think you should leave
the building first.

42
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:50,360
The security team is ready outside.
The other four units

43
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:53,720
are checking every corner for the shooter.

44
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:57,840
Let's go home. It's not safe here.

45
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:20,000
Where the hell did the files go?

46
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:35,000
The footage from the building cameras
during the incident is gone.

47
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:36,400
What about the street cameras?

48
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,400
None.

49
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:42,800
Someone ordered them deleted.

50
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,480
Who has that kind of power?

51
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:51,840
The bullets were aimed at me alone.

52
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,960
Who do you think did it?

53
00:06:57,520 --> 00:06:58,560
I don't know.

54
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:02,960
Or you do?

55
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,840
Did they catch the guy who shot Taiga?

56
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:17,960
Not yet.

57
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,400
Police are gathering all the evidence.

58
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:24,560
Mr. Naruban hasn't left the house.
A security team is on duty all the time.

59
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,240
What about Taiga?

60
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:30,160
At the hospital, checking on the injured.

61
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:34,720
Don't let him slip out of sight.

62
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:39,080
And Mr. Naruban?

63
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:42,000
It's fine. He's in a safe place

64
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,480
and already guarded.

65
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:46,160
Rin, go focus on Taiga.

66
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:12,760
The shooting news made 3C's stock drop.

67
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:14,760
Should we do something?

68
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:16,880
Since when do you care about the company?

69
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:20,440
I care about my husband.

70
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:26,960
Don't worry. PR will make sure
we're not tied to the shooting.

71
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:32,400
Who's that woman a victim for?
Who were they really trying to shoot?

72
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:36,000
I already sent flowers
and compensation money to the injured.

73
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,760
Sun.

74
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,960
How are you feeling?

75
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:05,760
These are flowers from 3C Corp.

76
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:12,800
Does it hurt much?

77
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:15,680
It hurts.

78
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:20,360
I'll tell the police
not to ask you anything yet.

79
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:28,520
Pat.

80
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,560
I'm sorry.

81
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:38,080
You're not the one who shot me.
Why apologize?

82
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,080
Because I've wronged you.

83
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:44,240
I've made you hurt in every way.

84
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:48,160
What if I don't forgive you?

85
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:53,560
I have to accept it because I was wrong.

86
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,480
I just want you to know,

87
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:03,720
Aru and I, we are nothing more
than old friends,

88
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:06,440
absolutely nothing else.

89
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:16,320
Hello, everyone!

90
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:18,600
Today,

91
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:23,960
if it's not on sale,
I'll just slash the price myself!

92
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:27,080
We're breaking the price on swimsuits!

93
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:31,320
Here it is. Summer's here.
Who's ready to hit the beach

94
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,920
looking hot and gorgeous?

95
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:37,920
Only 99 baht! Wow, crazy cheap!

96
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,640
Add to cart and grab yours, everyone!

97
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:43,800
While you're shopping,

98
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:46,440
I'll be reading your comments too!

99
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:50,040
"Really shipping, exactly like the pics!"

100
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:54,000
Someone already confirmed.
Grab yours, everyone!

101
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,960
{\an8}"Ex-con seller."

102
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,880
I'm not ex…

103
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:05,920
I'm not exaggerating.
I'm not lying to you.

104
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,760
Seriously, our stuff is top quality,
every single piece!

105
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,640
Okay, let's keep reading.

106
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:19,120
{\an8}SHE KILLED SOMEONE
WHY ONLY A SHORT TIME IN JAIL?

107
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,200
Whoa.

108
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:23,720
My throat's super dry.

109
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:26,960
I'm gonna take a quick break
and grab a drink.

110
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:31,040
We'll be back soon!

111
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:34,280
Alright, let's shut it down for now.

112
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:40,960
All the comments are insults.

113
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:44,920
It's like the IPs
were made just to attack you.

114
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:48,680
"Ex-con seller. Go to hell."

115
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:54,240
Then, let someone else
take over the livestream for now.

116
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:56,960
Got it.

117
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:06,000
Take it slow.

118
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:18,240
Even if you two have nothing going on,

119
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,240
I won't forgive you.

120
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:25,040
I'll drag her to hell
because you love her.

121
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:27,240
Pat!

122
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:29,400
What are you going to do to Aru?

123
00:12:32,880 --> 00:12:35,520
Thank you.

124
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:43,920
Aru, gorgeous!

125
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:51,120
I can do even more than this.

126
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,080
I thought we didn't need to be involved.

127
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:59,120
Aru, please.

128
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:04,080
Please what, Sun?
I'm minding my own business.

129
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:06,200
Yet she hired people to trash me online

130
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:08,720
and even threw paint at me.

131
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:12,880
Serves you right.
I was gonna trash-talk you myself.

132
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:16,120
Too bad I'm stuck hurt in bed.

133
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:19,640
Do you even realize what you've done?

134
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:27,280
What? I just removed
the thorn from my heart,

135
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:29,440
ripped it out of my life,

136
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:33,080
out of society.
You have no place in this world.

137
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:44,400
IN CASE OF FIRE, DO NOT USE THE ELEVATOR

138
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,360
You said you care about me,
that you worry about me.

139
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:31,000
Then kick her out! Get her out!

140
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:33,600
How could I even stand
being with a cruel woman like you?

141
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:35,560
Because you're a money-grubbing man!

142
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:39,840
My money didn't just buy you,
it bought your mom

143
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:41,080
and sister as well!.

144
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:43,000
- Pat!
- Go ahead!

145
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:45,000
If you're going to team up on me, do it!

146
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:49,440
Yeah, we didn't start out with love.

147
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:54,120
But I've been trying every day to build it
to make it what you wanted.

148
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:58,320
But making others suffer

149
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:01,280
doesn't heal the wounds of the past.

150
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:04,400
It only opens our wounds wider.

151
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:08,720
In the end, some things can't be fixed.

152
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:13,720
If you think you can buy me with money,

153
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:17,160
with no real connection,

154
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:22,280
today, your money means nothing to me.

155
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:23,920
Sun!

156
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:26,600
Sun. No, Sun!

157
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:29,000
I'm sorry for everything.

158
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:33,040
- Sun! Don't go, Sun!
- Miss Pat.

159
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,680
Sun!

160
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:37,560
Take care of yourself first.

161
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:42,400
Pat, that's enough, dear.

162
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,560
Mom.

163
00:15:45,640 --> 00:15:48,760
Sun, get out
of my daughter's life already.

164
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:50,400
How much money do you want? Tell me!

165
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:57,320
I've had enough.
The only one who still needs me is Pat.

166
00:15:57,920 --> 00:16:00,200
Mom, don't interfere.
I'll handle this myself.

167
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:04,360
I won't wait until things go too far,
until my daughter dies first.

168
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:06,240
That's good.

169
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:09,360
You love your daughter as you should.

170
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:15,200
Because a child grows on love,

171
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:20,000
not money, like you've been doing.

172
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:24,120
Even animals love their young.

173
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:27,560
A mother like you should understand that.

174
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,720
I've been suffering.

175
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:36,440
I've had to live
like no one else exists in this world.

176
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:41,440
Every day, I feel more worthless.

177
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:46,200
I know how much I owe you.

178
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:50,160
But I've lost
the most important thing in my life.

179
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:54,480
From now on,

180
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:58,720
I just want to live like a normal person.

181
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:00,560
Just go!

182
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:04,960
Don't cling to him.
I'll find someone better for you.

183
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:08,599
No, Mom. I want Sun! Mom, don't!

184
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:11,200
Mom, hold him back!
Why are you sending him away?

185
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,760
- Pat!
- Sun!

186
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:14,480
- No! Sun!
- Pat.

187
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:16,240
- Calm down, dear.
- Mom! Sun!

188
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:17,960
Let's end everything here.

189
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:24,040
If Mr. Sun still has anything pending,
send the list to my assistant.

190
00:17:24,119 --> 00:17:26,680
Mr. Sun is someone I know.

191
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:30,160
Sun. Sun!

192
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:32,120
- Sun! You can't go!
- Pat!

193
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,960
- No!
- Pat! My dear!

194
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:35,960
- No way!
- Pat!

195
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:37,320
I love you, Pat.

196
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:40,640
- From now on, I won't leave you alone.
- No!

197
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:44,040
Go after Sun! Sun belongs to me!

198
00:17:44,120 --> 00:17:46,400
Sun is mine! Sun!

199
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:47,440
- Sun!
- Pat!

200
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:50,200
Sun isn't yours.

201
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:53,680
He has his own life.

202
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:54,840
Sun is mine!

203
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:56,560
I want him!

204
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:58,280
- Sun is my toy!
- Pat.

205
00:17:58,360 --> 00:17:59,520
- Sun is my toy!
- Pat.

206
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:02,960
- I'll play with him!
- Sit down, Pat.

207
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:05,840
- Calm down, Pat.
- Sun, come back right now!

208
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:09,000
- Sun!
- Pat!

209
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:20,800
It's my fault.

210
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:26,840
You can start over anytime, Sun.

211
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:30,560
Even when I was in prison,

212
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:32,760
behind those walls,

213
00:18:34,320 --> 00:18:36,320
I never lost hope.

214
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:41,840
You had to go to jail
taking the blame for me.

215
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:47,600
I'm sorry.

216
00:18:57,280 --> 00:19:01,360
I don't dwell on the past.

217
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:06,520
I've moved on from the times
I was really hurting.

218
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:10,000
These days, I'm just Aru,

219
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:14,680
the online seller, selling stuff,
working every day,

220
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:18,520
earning my own money,
not relying on anyone.

221
00:19:22,240 --> 00:19:24,720
This is my life

222
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,400
and my pride.

223
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:31,600
Thank you.

224
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:30,040
My adoptive father, Mr. Kenji,

225
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:35,840
he died because he refused
to live under the rule of evil people.

226
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:44,000
My father was killed by Fire Phoenix.

227
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:52,880
I don't even know what Fire Phoenix is

228
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:56,720
and why they wanted my father dead.

229
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:04,080
Why didn't you try to find the truth?

230
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:17,960
There's no information
on what Fire Phoenix is.

231
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:23,600
All I know
is Fire Phoenix killed my father.

232
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:28,320
He was just a designer.

233
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:33,600
After the funeral, 3C Corp. contacted me.

234
00:21:39,520 --> 00:21:41,640
I thought work
would make me forget the pain.

235
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:18,480
Want to try?

236
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:15,600
<i>Welcome to the voicemail service.</i>

237
00:25:38,640 --> 00:25:42,080
If you ever want to paint,
you can come here anytime.

238
00:25:43,360 --> 00:25:45,200
Are you opening an art school?

239
00:25:49,160 --> 00:25:50,640
I can be a lot of things

240
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:52,120
if you want.

241
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:58,000
I'll take it.

242
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:01,160
I'll frame it for you.

243
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:04,600
No need. Thank you so much, Taiga.

244
00:26:08,560 --> 00:26:10,880
My pleasure, student.

245
00:26:31,080 --> 00:26:33,120
Hey, Rin. Today,

246
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:35,600
someone was lurking around
the front of the house.

247
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:40,080
I even took pictures.

248
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:43,160
Do you recognize whose car this is?

249
00:26:51,400 --> 00:26:52,440
Whose car?

250
00:26:53,280 --> 00:26:54,520
Huh?

251
00:26:57,160 --> 00:26:58,680
I'll go take a shower first.

252
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:19,960
Sorry I didn't answer.
I was at Taiga's house.

253
00:27:21,200 --> 00:27:24,360
He invited me, so I went.
It was an opportunity for us.

254
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:25,520
Did you find anything?

255
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:30,120
No. He was completely normal.

256
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:31,560
<i>I didn't see anything.</i>

257
00:27:34,080 --> 00:27:37,040
I'll find out what he's hiding.

258
00:27:37,120 --> 00:27:38,280
I trust you, Rin.

259
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:40,640
<i>Don't forget how your father died.</i>

260
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:43,840
Don't forget who brought you back to life.

261
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:47,440
I'm not trying to demand gratitude,

262
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:49,920
but I don't want my only niece
going down the wrong path.

263
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:52,920
<i>Don't let anyone see your weakness, Rin.</i>

264
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,760
Even matters of the heart

265
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:59,080
must be handled with your head.

266
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:30,400
Until now, we've got nothing.

267
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:33,640
Rin's just like any normal girl.

268
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:37,880
Normal? Is it because you
never really paid attention?

269
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:42,000
I know, but I have to find a way
to connect Rin to Fire Phoenix.

270
00:28:42,080 --> 00:28:45,040
And you let yourself be an easy target,
almost getting shot.

271
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:47,520
Lucky you survived.

272
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:52,000
At this rate, next time,
they'll come at you harder.

273
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,760
Until Fire Phoenix gets my body,

274
00:28:57,480 --> 00:28:59,840
I don't want anyone else
getting hurt because of me.

275
00:29:01,560 --> 00:29:02,800
That's gonna be tough.

276
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:11,920
Instead of running,
we have to lure them out.

277
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:14,880
Hunt them down every way we can.

278
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:25,320
Everyone's here.

279
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:28,800
So let's get started. Please.

280
00:29:32,120 --> 00:29:33,680
Hello, everyone.

281
00:29:33,760 --> 00:29:37,680
Thank you for taking the time
to join today's press conference.

282
00:29:38,480 --> 00:29:42,280
Our Cosmic Central Corporation Group
is honored to welcome Mr. Taiga,

283
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:47,840
the designer behind
the globally famous Kenji clothing brand,

284
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:52,200
as our signature designer
to create uniforms

285
00:29:52,280 --> 00:29:54,520
for our employees.

286
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:58,200
We are also launching
the smart application, Hi,

287
00:29:58,280 --> 00:30:00,480
a hub for shopping, talking,

288
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:05,160
and entertainment, bringing happiness
and prosperity to everyone.

289
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:24,160
The design concept
reflects the organization's identity.

290
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:25,880
Sleek, elegant,

291
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:28,400
leading in every investment,
with the vision

292
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:31,200
of being intelligent, powerful,
and confident.

293
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:35,600
<i>Next, please welcome Mr. Taiga.</i>

294
00:30:39,080 --> 00:30:39,880
Hello.

295
00:30:47,080 --> 00:30:51,120
The heart of this clothing design
is classic style,

296
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:56,440
to emphasize the stability of 3C Corp.

297
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:36,560
May I invite all executives
to take a group photo together?

298
00:31:37,440 --> 00:31:38,720
<i>Thank you very much.</i>

299
00:31:57,840 --> 00:31:58,720
Dad!

300
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:02,200
Dad!

301
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:13,520
Cheers!

302
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:23,520
Dad's press conference
didn't even last half an hour,

303
00:32:23,600 --> 00:32:26,880
and our 3C stock shot up 30%,

304
00:32:26,960 --> 00:32:28,400
hitting the ceiling price.

305
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:30,280
The profits are obvious.

306
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:32,280
Without the ceiling,

307
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:33,840
it would've gone over 100%.

308
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:36,200
Today's press conference went really well.

309
00:32:36,280 --> 00:32:38,920
The media interviewed Dad
for over an hour.

310
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:41,720
The uniform change was Nun's idea.

311
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:44,760
Keep going, dear.

312
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:47,000
Yes, thank you.

313
00:32:49,040 --> 00:32:50,480
I'll get back to work.

314
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:57,920
From now on, 3C-Coin

315
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:00,240
will make you a future world leader.

316
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:02,120
Alright.

317
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:06,600
Make it happen, Te.
Dad and I are waiting to celebrate.

318
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:10,320
I will, for sure. When it comes
to money, you can trust me.

319
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:13,560
I'll use every coin
to build our 3C empire.

320
00:33:16,680 --> 00:33:20,800
Thanks. You're the one
who planned the press conference.

321
00:33:22,560 --> 00:33:24,880
I had to do it for you.

322
00:33:36,720 --> 00:33:38,840
Go serve the room inside as well.

323
00:33:38,920 --> 00:33:40,040
Okay.

324
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:45,120
Alright. Prep these for me.

325
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:53,520
You know, my next project will let
everyone farm their way to wealth.

326
00:34:01,280 --> 00:34:03,240
- Sorry.
- Yes?

327
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:06,720
Could you take this inside to serve?
My stomach hurts.

328
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:08,000
Sure.

329
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:15,040
My 3C-Coin will soar,

330
00:34:15,639 --> 00:34:17,480
generating the highest profits.

331
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:19,960
You can use it to buy anything,

332
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:24,040
even a human's breath.

333
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:25,960
That's really interesting.

334
00:34:26,040 --> 00:34:27,120
Right?

335
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:31,520
Hey, aren't you going to the bathroom?

336
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:33,560
Oh, I'm going!

337
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:37,719
Techut was talking about 3C-Coin,

338
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:40,600
but it didn't sound
like it's just an investment.

339
00:34:41,440 --> 00:34:44,600
What does he mean by human breath?

340
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:50,120
To survive, humans need the basics,

341
00:34:50,199 --> 00:34:54,199
food, clothes, shelter, and…

342
00:34:56,239 --> 00:34:57,360
- Medicine!
- Medicine!

343
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:59,680
That's what I think.

344
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:03,480
Especially now, with pandemics,

345
00:35:03,560 --> 00:35:06,840
vaccines, serums, and medicine
are insanely valuable.

346
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:09,320
But 3C Corp. doesn't make medicine.

347
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:12,280
Doesn't make it or you just don't know?

348
00:35:15,360 --> 00:35:18,080
Rin, try to investigate.

349
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:21,680
Anything that comes out of Techut's mind,

350
00:35:21,760 --> 00:35:25,000
it's bound to be evil,
corrupt, and disastrous.

351
00:35:25,080 --> 00:35:28,760
Mr. Naruban wouldn't just let his son
do whatever he wants like that.

352
00:35:29,360 --> 00:35:31,040
Don't underestimate a madman, Rin.

353
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:36,040
Okay, I get that you have faith
in Mr. Naruban.

354
00:35:36,120 --> 00:35:39,520
But his son's definitely something else.

355
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:42,960
Anything we can stop,

356
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:45,480
we need to act before it's too late.

357
00:35:47,280 --> 00:35:49,720
Do you trust an ex-con like me?

358
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:54,320
The prison isn't for rich people.

359
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:06,520
I graduated in medical science.

360
00:36:06,600 --> 00:36:09,040
We're not hiring for this department.

361
00:36:11,080 --> 00:36:14,920
I can actually do a lot of different jobs,
even outside my degree.

362
00:36:18,280 --> 00:36:20,120
You have a conviction for murder.

363
00:36:22,720 --> 00:36:23,760
Yes.

364
00:36:27,720 --> 00:36:29,800
We'll get back to you.

365
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:31,480
Thank you.

366
00:36:45,640 --> 00:36:47,200
Can I see that application?

367
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:10,680
Yes?

368
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:15,120
You want me to come back
for another interview?

369
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:18,680
Okay, sure!

370
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:25,280
Looking at your application,
I was surprised.

371
00:37:26,680 --> 00:37:28,400
Surprised by what?

372
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:30,320
Everything.

373
00:37:44,680 --> 00:37:46,560
You're full of surprises.

374
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:50,840
We're not that close.

375
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:52,800
Even if we were,

376
00:37:53,640 --> 00:37:56,240
you have no right to touch me

377
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:58,400
without my permission.

378
00:38:07,720 --> 00:38:09,520
You want the job, don't you?

379
00:38:09,600 --> 00:38:12,400
I want it based on my skills,

380
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:14,200
not anything else.

381
00:38:15,680 --> 00:38:18,880
Don't do anything
that could count as sexual harassment.

382
00:38:19,560 --> 00:38:22,120
I could have you arrested.

383
00:38:38,240 --> 00:38:40,520
Mr. Naruban's looking for you.

384
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:14,880
Mr. Te.

385
00:39:16,400 --> 00:39:20,320
He said no need to meet anymore.
He's doing an online call to Europe now.

386
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:21,680
Online call?

387
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:24,720
Then why drag me here?

388
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:28,640
Stop meddling in everything
and messing up the timing.

389
00:39:29,600 --> 00:39:30,440
Mr. Te.

390
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:10,040
I really want to thank you, Mr. Taiga.

391
00:40:10,120 --> 00:40:13,840
I do what I'm supposed to.
It's no trouble.

392
00:40:16,560 --> 00:40:18,120
My mother

393
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:20,640
would like to host a meal for you.

394
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:24,120
No need, Ms. Nun.

395
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:27,880
I have to do my best, anyway.

396
00:40:30,760 --> 00:40:33,280
Please let me host you at my home.

397
00:40:35,920 --> 00:40:37,920
Don't refuse me, okay?

398
00:40:43,160 --> 00:40:44,320
Please.

399
00:40:47,400 --> 00:40:50,400
- Please, Taiga. I want to go too.
- Madam.

400
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,040
Taiga.

401
00:40:52,120 --> 00:40:54,600
- Madam.
- Stop throwing! That hurts!

402
00:40:58,880 --> 00:41:00,440
I want to go with you.

403
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:04,240
You need someone with you
in case something happens.

404
00:41:06,200 --> 00:41:08,640
Something will go wrong
because you are coming.

405
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:13,080
With your stubbornness, Taiga won't get
anything from Naruban's house.

406
00:41:13,160 --> 00:41:14,200
Shut up, you bear!

407
00:41:18,720 --> 00:41:21,800
Opportunities like this don't come easily.

408
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:26,040
You get to go into a tiger's den.
Just let Taiga do his job, Madam.

409
00:41:26,120 --> 00:41:27,480
Please, madam.

410
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:32,480
Please, Ratee.

411
00:41:33,080 --> 00:41:34,640
I'll handle this myself.

412
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:47,520
I'm tracking Punlop.

413
00:41:47,600 --> 00:41:50,480
If we find a connection between these two,

414
00:41:50,560 --> 00:41:52,000
Punlop and Rin,

415
00:41:53,400 --> 00:41:54,680
we can be sure

416
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:57,280
she serves Fire Phoenix.

417
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:59,360
That's why Naruban sent her to shadow you,

418
00:42:00,800 --> 00:42:02,680
ready to kill you at any moment.

419
00:42:12,360 --> 00:42:14,400
Stay strong, Taiga.

420
00:42:14,480 --> 00:42:17,400
A woman like Rin has no heart.

421
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:19,840
She'll do anything because it's an order.

422
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:22,920
I'm going to Naruban's house.

423
00:42:23,000 --> 00:42:25,960
Good. Then we can find a way
to confirm Naruban's identity.

424
00:42:30,800 --> 00:42:32,320
Fire Phoenix members

425
00:42:32,920 --> 00:42:34,800
must wear masks at every meeting.

426
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:37,280
Each mask

427
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:40,200
contains the code
for all of a member's information.

428
00:42:40,280 --> 00:42:42,040
I mean everything.

429
00:42:43,280 --> 00:42:46,560
Even things the member has forgotten,
Fire Phoenix still keeps.

430
00:42:47,400 --> 00:42:49,720
If we can get Naruban's mask,

431
00:42:51,480 --> 00:42:54,080
we'll be able to access
the heart of Fire Phoenix for sure.

432
00:43:10,680 --> 00:43:11,640
Who's going somewhere?

433
00:43:12,520 --> 00:43:13,840
It's Dad.

434
00:43:13,920 --> 00:43:17,520
He's got urgent investment business.
He has to go handle it.

435
00:43:20,320 --> 00:43:21,600
Is something wrong, dear?

436
00:43:23,400 --> 00:43:25,360
I invited Mr. Taiga over today,

437
00:43:25,440 --> 00:43:27,160
so I thought

438
00:43:27,240 --> 00:43:29,120
we could have a relaxed chat with him.

439
00:43:31,720 --> 00:43:33,520
I'm still here.

440
00:43:34,120 --> 00:43:37,200
Shall we give Mr. Taiga
a very special welcome?

441
00:43:39,280 --> 00:43:40,320
Yes.

442
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:48,240
They cut the building's power
without telling us, causing a surge

443
00:43:48,320 --> 00:43:50,880
that knocked out several CCTV servers.

444
00:43:50,960 --> 00:43:52,280
The backup power isn't enough.

445
00:43:53,520 --> 00:43:54,360
Let's go.

446
00:44:15,200 --> 00:44:16,240
Thanks.

447
00:44:21,840 --> 00:44:23,200
Mr. Taiga is here, Mom.

448
00:44:28,480 --> 00:44:29,760
Flowers for you.

449
00:44:30,280 --> 00:44:31,600
Thank you so much.

450
00:44:32,200 --> 00:44:34,360
Mr. Naruban had to fly to Europe
on urgent business.

451
00:44:35,240 --> 00:44:36,360
Understood.

452
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:39,320
We're so glad to have
the chance to welcome you.

453
00:44:43,520 --> 00:44:45,760
I heard Nun invited some friends over,

454
00:44:45,840 --> 00:44:47,760
so I invited Miss Ratee to join.

455
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:54,600
- Hello.
- Welcome.

456
00:44:54,680 --> 00:44:56,360
Your house is beautiful.

457
00:44:57,960 --> 00:44:59,840
My mom has great style.

458
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:02,840
She decorated all of this herself.

459
00:45:04,040 --> 00:45:07,400
This is why they say a man's power

460
00:45:07,480 --> 00:45:09,520
comes from the woman behind him.

461
00:45:10,240 --> 00:45:12,920
A happy family is the greatest thing.

462
00:45:13,000 --> 00:45:16,080
Just seeing Mr. Naruban
and the kids smile,

463
00:45:16,160 --> 00:45:19,120
that's enough to make my life complete.

464
00:45:20,600 --> 00:45:22,160
I'm so envious.

465
00:45:22,960 --> 00:45:25,360
Mr. Techut's family is so warm.

466
00:45:26,040 --> 00:45:28,760
I hear you're a great cook too.

467
00:45:28,840 --> 00:45:30,120
Oh.

468
00:45:30,200 --> 00:45:33,320
Good grief, are you gossiping
about me too?

469
00:45:33,920 --> 00:45:36,360
- Huh?
- Just a little.

470
00:45:37,680 --> 00:45:39,560
I'll excuse myself to the bathroom.

471
00:45:42,040 --> 00:45:43,200
This way, please.

472
00:45:49,600 --> 00:45:51,240
{\an8}This is the information Dad kept.

473
00:46:02,160 --> 00:46:03,920
{\an8}<i>The Blazing Tiger gang in Japan,</i>

474
00:46:04,520 --> 00:46:07,320
{\an8}they oppose Fire Phoenix.
They killed our people.

475
00:46:43,440 --> 00:46:45,120
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn

